rComments: If you are above average when it comes to general political knowledge, I highly suggest this professor since his lectures are so rich and impactful. If you have a hard time with politics then I would warn you to pay attention in class. NB: I've rarely seen professors that mastered the course content so well.

Take a course with this prof if you get a chance. Great lecturer and the readings were not too heavy. He is not the easiest marker, but he gives extremely good feedback. Recieved nearly 10 minutes of video feedback for my paper proposal which allowed for a much better term paper.

Prof Charbonneau was so-so, and his class is harder than average. The lectures were all right, but he doesn't use slides. The exams were tough, with a lot of questions from the readings, and you don't get any feedback to improve long-answer responses. We went into the final only knowing our midterm mark (20%), so this class caused a lot of stress.
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Very strict grader and the material is extremely heavy. He's a nice guy but has high expectations from a second-year class. You'll receive two papers worth 40% of your grade each. Not worth it. Just don't do it

This prof was very engaging and I learned a lot from his class. However, the lectures were pretty heavy. I found that the grading for the exam and midterm was a bit strict seeings as the prof had specific expectations for each question. But the paper was graded easier. You really have to know your stuff.

He does not provide slides or any visuals. Honestly, he's a good guy but he grades too heavily and cares about grammatical errors, even the minor ones. He has very heavy lectures and it's easy to lose track. Too many philosophers to study and the final is based on everything you learned in the semester. Just don't do it, your GPA will drop.

tbh prof is not bad. HOWEVER, some of the worst grades I have ever gotten. TAs are horrible and took nearly 2 months to get an essay grade back. went into final with only 20% of my grade... exam was brutal. just terrible.
Amazing prof., probably one of my favorites. Super funny and he gave us an extra week for a project which was needed!
The guy rickrolled the entire class with a link in an email he sent. Absolute legend.

This is the second class I've had him and I hope I'll continue to get him in the future. He's a bit of a tougher marker but his lectures and just overall personality makes it worth it. Super engaging, super caring towards his students - really wants you to succeed. Gave me a 10 minute video with super helpful feedback! I LOVE HIM????

literally the best prof ever. he makes class interesting, a poli sci students dream. you don't have to go because he records himself but being there makes it that better. no laptops/powerpoint but honestly that part doesn't matter. just listen and learn. cheat sheet available for exams too!

By far one of the best professors at the university! He cares about his stuff, and teaches it in an incredibly easy to understand way. I have taken 4 classes with him and would take 10 more if I could. 10/10 recommend.

Very passionate and knowledgeable prof, old school way of teaching makes lectures engaging and interesting. Only downside is that he's a very tough grader and will criticize your work harshly if you have differing views - just graduated & this class was the worse grade I got in uni.

Mr. Charbonneau est toujours disponible pour répondre à vos questions (par juste par courriel mais au bureau aussi). Il enregistre tout ses cours et les met sur BS. Il est passionné et laisse 2 pages de notes à l'examen. La rédaction vallait 50% mais la rétroaction verbale individuelle sur le plan aide beaucoup.
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Graded by few things', 'Amazing lectures ']

rComments: An absolute gem of a prof - he records his lectures for you to listen back later or if you miss a class. No slides, but he teaches so well that you don't need them. One of the only professors I could listen to for 3 hours and not get bored - would happily have him read me the phone book. Best prof hands down

probably the best prof I've had in my 4 years. He's hilarious and kind and makes complicated material so engaging/ easy to understand. One of the few profs that held my attention the whole 3 hours. There was only one essay and the final but both were easy if you went to class. I would take a class with him again in a heartbeat- love the guy

This guy is a gem. He records all of his lectures so you can skip/access it whenever, and he's a pretty funny guy. A lot of the criticism on this page comes from the fact that he doesn't allow technology, but lots of political science professors don't. Taking notes by hand helps you learn, and he gives you recordings so you don't miss anything.

One of the best lecturers I have been fortunate to have in university thus far. His classes are fan-flipping-tastic, and I have learned so much. He breaks down some of the toughest philosophers works into simple, and comparable pieces. Great presentation skills, he uploads his lectures if you miss a class or need to catch up. Definitely worth it.

il donne des lectures grande assez et compliqué, mais j'en ai pas lu trop et je me suis sorti bien. l'examen mi-session est correcte mais il corrige sévèrement. le projet de session est long, prend du temps, difficile assez (a baissé ma note) l'examen final était facile car il donnait des choix de réponse(monté ma note) laisse usé des cheat sheets
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Get ready to read', 'Lecture heavy']

rComments: Amazing professor! He's incredibly passionate and knowledgeable about the topic. He records his lectures, and lets you take "cheat sheets" into the exam. He also is super understanding, and will give extensions if enough people ask for one. Clear lectures, clear expectations, interesting to listen to. Definitely recommend.

J'ai aimé les méthodes d'enseignement de M. Charbonneau et dans ses exams, qui sont cependant corrigés un peu sévèrement, il offre des choix de questions longues et les questions à choix multiples sont faciles. Le prof était aussi assez sympathique et enregistrait ses cours pour les mettre sur BB, ce qui est avantageux si on a à manquer un cours.

I liked him as a person, just not so much as a professor. He knows his subject really well and the class is pretty interesting, but it was hard to stay focused on the somewhat boring content. This is an intro class so it's not the profs fault, but still.

Charboneau is an amazing lecturer. However, he hates all electronic things so there was no powerpoint and no computers allowed. You need to work for your mark. Do not speak english in his class! Be respectful when you interact with him if you want him to take you seriously. I would take his class again if given the choice

Overall interesting class. He's very energetic, and he can be quite funny. No computers or phones allowed in class, and the notes are not available on Blackboard. Work is corrected pretty efficiently.
Great prof! Does not allow laptops and does not use powerpoint or blackboard. However he is an amazing lecturer. One essay, a midterm (one cheat sheet allowed) and a final(two cheat sheets allowed).

Lectures are confusing. Often hard to know what is important to put down on your notes. It feels like he assumes you to follow his train of thought when he goes off on tangents (in which I never did), making lectures even more confusing.

Je recommande ce professeur à tout le monde. J'ai adoré le contenu et personnellement, je n'apprécie pas nécessairement la technologie donc j'adore le fait qu'il ne l'utilise pas. Aussi, les lectures sont importantes et la présence en classe aussi. Il m'a donné le goût d'en apprendre encore plus sur la science politique. Je le recommande à 100%.

He's not bad, but like he kinda tries way too hard to be funny. Which isn't even funny most of the time. HIS USE OF 0 technology in class is ridiculous, we are in 2016... And there's just notes after notes.... Ruined my political science experience. Class is also boring. Wouldn't recommend taking his class, unless it's mandatory.

This prof is still old school, no laptops  or cellphones allowed. He does not put up powerpoints or anything on blackboard so its quite hard to keep up sometimes. He has no problem calling you out in front of the whole class which is kinda embarassing...

Il est un prof avec des techniques du bon vieux temps. Il place habituellement 4 ou 5 points au tableau et les biffes quand il termine. Ce cours n'avait jamais d'images pour appuyer le matériel. Il est gentil, mais les test sont pas si facile pour un cours de première année.
teacherRatingTags: ['Tough grader', 'Get ready to read', 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: Very eloquent, so the lectures are very interesting, especially for a first year introduction course. Good sense of humour and it's obvious he wants the best for the students. Would absolutely recommend to anyone. Not a tough grader, as long as you listen and do the readings, you'll get your A ;)

Very knowleadgeable and passionate professor. Downside is his unwillingness to use visual aids at all, so it's necessary to take a lot of notes. He speaks very fast and uses advanced vocabulary, so if french isnt your first language, you'll have a hard time but you will learn alot. All in all, good guy but just wish he was easier to understand

Il connait très bien sa matière et est passioné. Il n'utilise pas d'aide visuels, donc il faut vraiment écouter et prendre beaucoup de notes. Il encourage fortement les "cheat sheet" lors des examens, et donne presque toujours le choix de question pendant les examens. Bon sens d'humour et asser interessant à écouter.
AMAZING PROF. Always ready to help, very clear with hilarious yet relevant anecdotes. Talks fast, but always willing to help out FLS students. Take his class without hesitation.

Amazing prof. Extremely knowledgeable and friendly. Lectures are captivating,well organised, & easy to follow. Readings are not demanding but are absolutely essential. Old school guy; no computers allowed for note taking. Not the kind of class you can skip out on, not that you'll want to. Fair grading and no surprises. Would absolutely recommend.
Le meilleur professeur que j'ai eu! Bon orateur, a l'écoute de ses étudiants, et connait sa matière. Ses exigences sont clairs.
Awesome teacher! Very charismatic and willing to help students.His lectures are interesting and gives the best examples. Would take another class with him as a teacher any time!

Really great prof! He really enjoys his subject, and he uses great example and humour when teaching. He's a good prof to have if you're in french immersion as he pushes you to write in French, but will mark grammar at a slightly lower level if you let him know.

Incredibly helpful and charismatic, very busy guy but always willing to make time to help students. I would reccommend skipping TAs and going straight to him for questions, he gives clear, helpful answers and gives structured and fascinating lectures
great teacher, really interesting
He is such a nice and interesting prof! I love his sense of humour and he has great control of his classroom. All this being said, he's a tough grader, and uses very advanced vocabulary.
Really solid prof, knows his stuff, teaches reaaly well. no pwer poiint, but still a really good class if you want to learn something.

C'est un bon enseignant et ses examens semblent faciles, mais il est très pointilleux! Il possède toutefois beaucoup d'heures de bureau et il a plusieurs assistants disponibles. Il est important d''être présent aux cours..
Awesome teacher. Super interesting, best examples! I found it was amazing that he ALWAYS answers questions right away. Will definitely be taking another one of his classes.

Charbonneau est formidable comme prof! Les cours magistraux étaient tellement intéressants, les examens et le travail écrit étaient vraiment bien faits et les commentaires très utiles et pertinents. J'apprécie aussi le manque de technologie dans ses cours (pas de Campus virtuel, pas de diaporamas); il parle, et il le fait très bien. Recommandé!
Take this class without hesitation. He's a really good prof + funny.
Good Prof, but very boring! If you dont pay attention, it's easy to loose interest. Make sure you have a good understanding of the course prior to the exam!
Vraiment un bon prof! Ses exams sont moins pires qu'on pourrait s'y attendre mais il faut prendre beaucoup de notes et écouter en classe.

Excellent prof! J'ai adoré prendre son cour. Ses examens ne sont pas impossibles, il rend la matière intéressante avec de bons exemples et annecdotes. Il a un bon sens d'humour et réponds très bien aux questions posées en classe. Un prof à recommander!

charbonneau est un des meilleur prof en science politique..Il est tress claire, il prends son temps pour repondre aux questions ...et ses examins ne sont pas compliqué..je voudrais prendre autre cours avec lui ..
Great prof! Provided lecture outlines on the board that made note taking a breeze. Definitely take his political thought courses.
Un prof EXCELLENT. Passionné, aidant, stimulant, exigeant, mais drôle. Fortement recommandé: il possède réellement les qualités d'une bon prof.
This prof is awsome: passionate, hilarious at times, and very interesting. Makes the heavy load of course as light as a feather!

He is a fantastic prof. His lectures are fast paced and stimulating. He made me want to study Political Science again. People who have had trouble in his class or complain about him not finishing sentences should learn to listen and write at the same time. Just because you can't keep up doesn't mean he's not a wonderful professor.

Very good intro course. He loves what he's teaching, and it's really obvious. He is clear and explains things from a variety of angles. As long as you show up to class, you should have no problem at all.
Le prof. Charbonneau est vraiment bien. Ses cours sont clairs. La amtière est un peu difficile quand même mais le cours est bon.

Prof Charbonneau connait vraiment sa matière. Dont BS the guy. Il est asses "old school" (il écrit au tableau) mais le cours est vraiment clair. He's always nice when dumb people ask stupid questions...
Il est vraiment bien.
Hes really nice and funny, and knows what hes talikng about.
Good prof.
He was an okay prof. He really knows his stuff but he is unable to communicate efficiently. Overall : okay - needs to learn to finish his sentences before starting a new one!!!

The teacher runs on uselessly about some things that really don't make any sense with what he was originally trying to say. Very hard to take notes because he always rethinks his sentences and so you must re-write.
I had him for francophony en ontario.  Really boring subject, but he made it really interesting.  Verygood prof.

Really good prof, always ready to help.  He knows his stuff: don't even try to bs him.  I couldnt care less for the American Revolution b4 I took his class, but its hard not to be interested.  the guy is passionate about this stuff. Student debates were a waste of time.

Great Prof!Great Lectures..knew his material inside out!I had him for POL 4300: The American Revolution, very interesting course.Very helpful prof and he was also a fair marker.Would definitely take another course taught by him.
